OL,3,CGreen Party's Zoe Garbett elected as
OL,4,Cnew Hackney Mayor
OL,6,FThe Green Party's Zoe Garbett has
OL,7,Fvowed she will "change the system",
OL,8,Fafter being elected mayor of Hackney.
OL,10,FThe win ousted Labour, which has held
OL,11,Fthe mayoralty since the directly-
OL,12,Felected position was created in 2002.
OL,14,FSpeaking after the results, Ms Garbett
OL,15,Fsaid: "Today we start a fightback.
OL,26,@kD@QxrnD@UxroD@POUoD@bO]wD@GOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/7
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1778256667
OL,3,CGreen Party's Zoe Garbett elected as
OL,4,Cnew Hackney Mayor
OL,6,F"In this election, over and over,
OL,7,Fpeople kept telling me that they felt
OL,8,Flet down. People kept saying, 'it's
OL,9,Fhard for me and it's hard for us'.
OL,10,FCouncil services are failing those who
OL,11,Fneed them most and people are
OL,12,Fstruggling to make ends meet.
OL,14,F"To everyone who voted for me, I truly
OL,15,Fthank you for putting your trust in me
OL,16,Ftoday."
OL,18,FThe Greens took a decisive victory
OL,19,Fwith 35,720 votes, beating Labour by
OL,20,Fnearly 10,000.
OL,26,@kD@QxrnD@AOUvD@AOUxD@GO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/7
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1778256667
OL,3,CGreen Party's Zoe Garbett elected as
OL,4,Cnew Hackney Mayor
OL,6,FMs Garbett added: "I'm going to change
OL,7,Fthe system. That's why you've elected
OL,8,Fme, to lead the fightback here in
OL,9,FHackney, this campaign has never just
OL,10,Fbeen about the Green Party.
OL,12,F"Countless people, movements,
OL,13,Forganisations, parties and communities
OL,14,Fhave come together to make this change
OL,15,Fpossible."
OL,17,FDefeated former Labour mayor of
OL,18,FHackney Caroline Woodley - who
OL,19,Freceived 26,685 votes, said the Labour
OL,20,Fgovernment "has got a lot of work to
OL,21,Fdo. She also congratulated Ms Garbett.
OL,26,@kD@QxrnD@SOUtD@AOUwD@JO]|D@LOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/7
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,405,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F404A1778256667
OL,3,CGreen Party's Zoe Garbett elected as
OL,4,Cnew Hackney Mayor
OL,6,F"To Zoe, you've shown great
OL,7,Fdetermination and resilience, and I
OL,8,Fknow you have the support of the
OL,9,Fcouncil to continue the good work we
OL,10,Fhave done as a liberal administration."
OL,12,FMs Woodley added: "To my Labour
OL,13,Fgovernment, you've got a lot of work
OL,14,Fto do, but thank you for the
OL,15,Finvestment in housing."
OL,17,FLeader of the Green Party Zack
OL,18,FPolanski said "the country has clearly
OL,19,Frejected you" when asked for his
OL,20,Fmessage to Sir Keir Starmer.
OL,26,@kD@QxrnD@AOUtD@SOUwD@WO]zD@OOU{D@MO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/7
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
